  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Desert Locust Response in South Omo, Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Provision of four types of insecticides and associated accessories and safety material to fill government capacity. These will include; Malathion 95% 210 litres, Bust field 191 litres, Dymatot 210 litres, Highway 210 litres and Diaznon 70 kg. Along with the insecticides necessary accessories and safety equipment including safety clothes, goggles, masks and gloves in addition to knapsacks. Prior to undertaking spraying, plant protection experts from the Ministry of Agriculture will conduct technical training to community and volunteers on health and safety measures in the use of chemicals.
 
2) Provision of emergency seeds that involve 279.67 quintals of maize and 72.75 quintals of sorghum and 15 quintals of grass seeds. This will help to recover 1,469 hectares of crop land and 100 hectares of range/pasture lands. The seeds will be distributed in May and September 2020 following planting season/window after locust infestation fully controlled.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project demonstrated positive results in terms of  locust control and livelihood recovery</narrative>
  </description>
